Introduction

This is the first release of Amiga Hexen, the Amiga version of
the game by Raven Software.


Requirements

	o an 060. It may run on a 040 with FPU, but it will be too slow.
	  (There's no assembler in it).

	o a Hexen wad file. The shareware wadfile must be used with the
	  -shareware commandline option, ie.

		Hexen -shareware

	o rtgmaster.library (available on aminet)

	o 8 MB RAM


Features
	o Keyboard/Mouse/Joystick
	o Network (untested)
	o *no* sound yet


Installation
	After unpacking, copy a hexen.wad file into the Hexen directory.


Usage and commandline options

	Start Hexen by typing Hexen <options>, where options may be one
	of the following:

	-sharware   enable shareware workarounds
	-mouse      enable mouse support
	-joy        enable joystick support (needs lowlevel.library)
	-net        enable network
	For more options, refer to the README file that comes with
	the Hexen demo, or the Hexen manual


